                    <p>
                        <strong>
                            Financial reports give you detailed information about the instantaneous activities of the departments in your company. AWith these reports; your sales amounts in the middle of the month, which product you should sell more, which product is more profitable, how often you consume your stocks, which stocks you consume more slowly, what are the actual costs of the products or services you sell, which products should I develop in, or in which departments should I develop? respond all important output about your company. In addition, a management report designed according to the nature of your business, shows you what your situation is instantly.. In addition to all these, in order to manage your assets correctly, the cash flow statement, how many days you have collected your receivables, how long you have paid your debts, and seeing what kind of loss your company has incurred while performing all these transactions are very important points for your company’s efficiency.
